g.text: Druids hold court to determine whether or not to lock up a tiefling child for stealing their precious artifact. If you fail to stop it, the child tries to run and is attacked by their guardian snakes.
Sagha the druid leader is the main player in this scene. She is machiavellian, and flips to evil should the snakes attack the child.

g.title: n0478f5bf94c41bf4a5566f7b5bc56c55
g.text: |Here's my opinion about attacking the snake court.|

g.title: n9593790f4e935aa6adbc29e80fc2e39a
g.text: She eats our food, drinks our water. Then steals our most holy Idol in thanks!

g.title: nbd3b7c4e546c12e00714fae7662e6b85
g.text: Bury the remains. Continue the rite.

g.title: ne379c35e69790637f6baace6049a0281
g.text: Halsin is gone - I am First Druid now. I will take control and prove my authority.

g.title: n08cefaa7a4c129debe247908428d51eb
g.text: Rath - lock her up. She remains here until the rite is complete.

g.title: n430694e95ed22f520598898cde99d376
g.text: And keep still, devil. Teela is restless.

g.title: n0b5ca4a6aadb9e7a49713dc8d1663ce6
g.text: The words of the Treefather, spoken plain.

g.title: n0cff5d6aef88bda14360acc99327e0e8
g.text: The parasite eats our food, drinks our water. Then steals our most holy Idol in thanks!

g.title: n12272a0a855ab21c0b9809b20ad8e18d
g.text: No - the tiefling remains until the rite is complete.

g.title: n1737500c0692c10e7f848f3ac6074a36
g.text: Very well - she may go. Break your word, and my serpent shall feed.

g.title: n1dd7c3e56bce255ab2400277a55f32bb
g.text: She eats our food, drinks our water. Then steals our most holy Idol in thanks!

g.title: n2332fe66c311d1a62242b0e8f3021193
g.text: Thank you, Kagha. Master Halsin would...

g.title: nde3dca5b7b9d2350cf85ce958bca987b
g.text: Halsin isn't here. Keep his name off your tongue, lest Teela pierce it.

g.title: n235caa659d394f1b725fb13265c17988
g.text: A seed nobly sown renders the sweetest fruit. Be noble - set her free.

g.title: n61012382c6fc97e2ee0ec6145e734218
g.text: The devil sowed chaos. She remains until the rite is complete!

g.title: n294a7eeb519b359425a7de0a08684337
g.text: Don't be a coward. We could take them. We could kill them all.

g.title: n4325f0ae30a605fe30450a271e5c9bb9
g.text: And I will cast out the rest.

g.title: nf2058cc854fbeeb8086abddbe7e042ee
g.text: You intrude on the Circle. You intrude on my

g.title: n312b5259183ccab64ea2f2ef28d5a550
g.text: She's not a disease - she's a child.

g.title: nde3ee47e7dd52d2cfbb9e4139d20d5e2
g.text: They are a blight, each and all. If I cannot choke it out, I will burn it away.

g.title: n3381a141c93ee10a73f16c2450d62cf2
g.text: Release her. I'll see that she stays out of trouble.

g.title: n6442f3e1b7dac49b5692b833b4a1cc21
g.text: Don't druids cherish harmony? Jailing the girl disrupts nature's balance.

g.title: n39d9e865e21b64bc447e6618724d4723
g.text: You're no healer. And you're no judge either. Let her go.

g.title: nd858bc41b48bca5e6ef2f1b4eed6a220
g.text: The blight must be cut away for healing to begin. First, the spawn. The rest will follow.

g.title: n3b076c5f8185cfeed1e5abbee85291ac
g.text: You know, then, that Silvanus spoke further. 'The parasite must be removed for new seed to grow.'

g.title: nc0bc72b49c3857a5df3742255338db14
g.text: Yet behold: the parasite lives! She eats our food, drinks our water. Then steals our most holy Idol in thanks!

g.title: n811e55e696ad277edbfc2b0c550f91b5
g.text: I've heard enough. The devil remains until the rite is complete!

g.title: nf10b14d0f534a0ad4a7dd70ff72d9c4a
g.text: Come, Kagha. We took back the Idol. Surely...

g.title: n7898d481af2536964b7b2a1fdb0db3cf
g.text: To reject the helpless is to reject Silvanus himself.

g.title: n81d1cf46835c304e239f2e7c2114e7a2
g.text: One of your guards outside said you wanted to see me. Here I am.

g.title: nd3ee4158c200f3e5b9045b08cc6a3d90
g.text: The Blade of Frontiers has arrived. Explain this cruelty!

g.title: nd506e93cacc2027c68af972472ce3839
g.text: Imprison her? She's just a child.

g.title: n5362aeb40b82688a44696f0fe39fb974
g.text: Tell the snake to be at ease. The girl must not be harmed.

g.title: n7e55ea81ba609cf355f0c8a39ef50f1a
g.text: A seed nobly sown renders the sweetest fruit. Be noble - set her free.

g.title: n82ec9ed332ff1ff9ca1c5eded423f699
g.text: You've proven your authority. Now prove your mercy.

g.title: n8fa92550cabc008df8cd588a8a5b9c68
g.text: Don't druids cherish harmony? Jailing the girl disrupts nature's balance.

g.title: n988a8142e98e1edfb550f0295b9604b0
g.text: Release her. I'll see that she stays out of trouble.

g.title: nb6c2c909f8edea640873f8b7df3f3bb8
g.text: The girl is no threat. Jailing her disrupts nature's balance.

g.title: nc98a8ebfda4ce63775a97b721d297c68
g.text: Release her. I'll see that she stays out of trouble.

g.title: n53526aab51994c6e0923ea555067fcfe
g.text: Tell me, Blade. Is the healer cruel for ridding the sick of disease?

g.title: n9411f5d1af1cf2fc446ca0cf66fa2c78
g.text: This isn't my kind of justice... but I won't stand in your way.

g.title: nfc73c2c0142dbe9c8f132ed7298c8d0c
g.text: Silence. I answer only to mistress.

g.title: n5f5ba4ba0c079d90cc0d7d9582c2fd37
g.text: Perhaps you don't know that Silvanus spoke further. 'The parasite must be removed for new seed to grow.'

g.title: n5f64ed7cc8fb02cd22517d93d723d489
g.text: Hold on! It's not too late to settle this without bloodshed.

g.title: n61d2668e9cabdbd21bf45af4e22d5d62
g.text: The Treefather's words. Your circle taught well.

g.title: n659e5833a8292a80d3b68eb1af38d0b9
g.text: Let judgement be cast. Spill blood after, if you must.

g.title: n6be479d4e5f7506352df4e7aea681690
g.text: |Here's my opinion about attacking the snake court.|

g.title: n709c463dbcc10c943c8ced294b929328
g.text: And the parents? They're just outside...

g.title: n9684a400b5fc60be5440e156e85371e6
g.text: will take word once I've spoken to him. We must focus on the rite.

g.title: n7fff3b631deae81177d2f6d618158138
g.text: Out, thief. My grace has its limits.

g.title: nab4821226d22b817ebb2c4465103d8ae
g.text: Good. Play nice until we get what we need.

g.title: nd07520cfaee1e062e6d3fce4eb0dcc04
g.text: A fickle one, aren't you? I hope you know what you're doing.

g.title: ndc904b9eef6968861f53b4a7411f4885
g.text: Good. Let's focus on the girl first. We can settle with the snake later.

g.title: n74fd30791fa3e0c54e708c9d2952d9fb
g.text: Gone. By the gods, Kagha, what have you

g.title: nd4734403e1f49054ad1f7ee5b9682994
g.text: The Treefather's words spoken with a devil's forked tongue.

g.title: nb1525bdc612bc15175949f151cb08d60
g.text: We will speak soon enough. First, judgement must be passed.

g.title: nee1d276525304f7aa4c544f8d2c09ba4
g.text: Fair words. Child, take to the others word of my grace.

g.title: nff9e3438d6ebe19c8c48b374449525ff
g.text: Rath - lock her up. She remains here until the rite is complete.

g.title: n9fa73005a0c2f2725b55fd4642e1b1ab
g.text: This Kagha's barbaric. The Blade's got your back.

g.title: nf10c3888c4825b93d4d7fc807830e633
g.text: This is madness, Kagha. She's just a...

g.title: nf7efecb80e31a2219284e45d640f157c
g.text: It is as I feared - the tiefling strikes on Zevlor's behalf! Call the Circle to arms - we will cleanse the grove of parasites, once and for all.

g.title: ned910f35677f78f510f293ee38838623
g.text: |Here's my opinion about attacking the snake court.|

g.title: nc9501092d8c358a9a82b8deb2663ff22
g.text: More proof that outsiders must never be trusted.

g.title: ne216850160907daed54365958366547b
g.text: And keep still, devil. Teela is restless.

g.title: nf665bfbf94f8a9a612bc8bec358eb278
g.text: I hear the Treefather's spirit in your words.
